   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>News Roundup:</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>Where are we going, and why am I in this handbasket?</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Coray</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">08/20/2003 01:00 PM CDT &nbsp;&nbsp; 6 Comments</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText">First off the third <a href="http://www.gamespy.com/interviews/august03/ldon3/" target="_new">interview</a> Gamespy has posted with Absor and this one features less bad questions, but also doesn't really give much detail. I suppose I'm after things that you don't normally learn from interviews, and only from playing but I come away from these interviews not feeling like I learned much.<p>Next up on the interview circuit is <a href="http://www.homelanfed.com/index.php?id=16382" target="_new">Robert Pfister</a> mostly dealing with general game and LDoN questions. It really doesn't reveal much new information and is more a recap with the same old questions that have been answered dozens of times.<p>All of that sort of ties in with the unveiling of the third type of LDoN dungeon, <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/lostdungeons/dungeons_miragul.jsp" target="_new">Miraguls Menagerie</a>. Aside from the three sentance overview..<p><strong>Deep within the frozen tundra, magic has taken on a form of its own. As Miragul's cursed form walks on the frigid ground above, his menagerie of artifacts and arcane knowledge secretly awaits his return. Created through the use of magic, this lair now seeks power of its own. Do you have strength to harness power that waits beneath the ice... or will you become another specimen in Miragul's collection?</strong><p>There are a variety of screenshots. My summary of the shots are as follows. Scary looking whirlwind thing, Halfling standing behind a goblin, Barbarian and Halfling staring down a hallway, four pictures of that crazy duo fighting a skeleton thing, and then two pictures of them fighting a spider in velketors castle.<p>Also there are more <a href="http://eq.stratics.com/content/features/ldon.shtml" target="_new">screenshots</a> on EQStratics, the new ones being the ice ones, not the dozen pictures of boxes and are generally the same or similar to the ones shown on the official site, and <a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/news/sdetail2149.html?story=2149" target="_new">Allakhazam</a> has a series of pictures which are actually very helpful in understanding how the item augmentation system works along with even more Miraguls screenshots.<p>Just three weeks until LDoN is supposed to go live, so I would expect to hear a bit more about the last two areas between now and then.<p><BIG>No sprinkles! For every sprinkle I find, I shall kill you!</BIG><p>Moving on from Everquest news for a bit, we'll take a look at what Moorgard has had to say since our last update about Everquest 2. <a href="http://www.everquest-2.com/phpbb/viewtopic.php?p=66248&amp;highlight=&amp;sid=e17706f30b496e68c4acac2cd3a7cccf#66248" target="_new">First up</a> is the fact it'll take more than two people to kill Nagafen (or any big thing)..<p><strong>That sequence was a demo displayed months ago that was designed solely to show how cool the dragon is. That's all it was indicative of. Naturally it will take much more effort to defeat the real thing.</strong><p>To which people said that they couldn't have more than two people because the game runs so slow! On where you can start depending on your <a href="http://www.everquest-2.com/phpbb/viewtopic.php?p=66231&amp;highlight=&amp;sid=e17706f30b496e68c4acac2cd3a7cccf#66231" target="_new">alignment</a>..<p><strong>If you're an evil race, only Freeport will accept you. If you're a race that can be either good or evil, then your choice comes down to which city you swear allegiance to. If you're neutral, then you'll be neutral, although you'll still have to swear allegiance to a city.</strong> <p>About <a href="http://www.everquest-2.com/phpbb/viewtopic.php?p=66968&amp;highlight=&amp;sid=e17706f30b496e68c4acac2cd3a7cccf#66968" target="_new">Instancing</a> in EQ2..<p><strong>Instancing will not be a real common thing. We'll use it to alleviate potential bottlenecks or to personalize content, not to make it seem like you're the only person in the world. </strong><p>And..<p><strong>That doesn't mean serving it to you on a silver platter, it means presenting it in a way that as much as possible prevents real-world logjams from interfering with your immersion in the game. </strong><p>A good thing, also the common sense thing given the idea is to play with other people. And finally actual information pertaining to how banks work. For a long time it was reported that each bank was different so you couldn't go to the Freeport bank and get an item out that you put in the Qeynos bank. Needless to say, that's not a lot of fun, and it has a number of other downsides. Moorgard <a href="http://www.everquest-2.com/phpbb/viewtopic.php?p=66887&amp;highlight=&amp;sid=e17706f30b496e68c4acac2cd3a7cccf#66887" target="_new">updates</a> us all on the status of that idea..<p><strong>We decided this was an unnecessary burden. It wasn't fun. So, we changed it. </strong><p><strong>Banks will be universal. Your bank is your bank--period.</strong><p>Which is good news for everyone.<p><BIG>You're so money and you don't even know it!</BIG><p>After reading all the news and <em>exclusives</em> everyone else was getting, I was starting to feel left out. Just about that time, I happened to check my email, and I happened upon an email from my <strong>good</strong> friends at Sony that thankfully does not have a bunch of screenshots, because quite frankly, it's far more entertaining to see things with your own eyes. That's right, they are going to let me pick 10 Mobhunter readers who will get to participate in the LDoN Beta test.<p>After some internal debate, I've decided that you <a href="mailto:ldoncontest@hotmail.com?Subject=LDON Contest" target="_new">must tell ME</a> why you deserve to be in the beta test. Write a one paragraph explanation and I will pick my favorite 10 and those people will get into the beta. <strong>Please make SURE to include your first and last names, along with your Station Name (</strong><em><strong>NOT YOUR PASSWORD! </strong></em><strong>) or your entry will not count since those are things Sony requires. </strong><p>The deadline for submissions is Friday the 22nd at 5 PM PST. At some point over the weekend I will post the winning entries and submit the names to Sony and hopefully they can get everyone started early next week.<p>I encourage you to be creative with it, and good luck.<p>On a somewhat related note, everyone should keep an eye out next week for my hands on preview of the expansion!</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
